						<summary>

						<p>On a slab leaning against a wall of the Śankaraliṅga temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 12th Century.</p>						

						<p>This inscription refers itself to the reign of a Chālukya king whose name is lost. It seems to register several gifts including an oil mill for a perpetual lamp to the god Śaṅkara by the <hi rend="italic">Mahājanas</hi> of the <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> and others. The epigraph is damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
